1
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,440
Was it you who took the truck
and tried to steal the sheep?

2
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,720
Who would waste time
stealing their own property?

3
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:30,880
What the hell does that mean?

4
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,280
Foul language? So we're close now?

5
00:02:34,720 --> 00:02:36,080
<i>Did that catch you off guard,</i>

6
00:02:36,160 --> 00:02:38,160
<i>my beloved stepmother?</i>

7
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:39,640
Mr. Yai.

8
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:41,200
<i>What's going on, Noi?</i>

9
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:43,440
<i>Well, he was a robber.</i>

10
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:46,720
But now he's the heir to Paisal Farm!

11
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:48,840
Mr. Yai came back?

12
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:51,160
Or…

13
00:02:52,160 --> 00:02:54,840
do you want me to pick up
from where we left off last night?

14
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:02,440
Pin! You think you can run from me?

15
00:03:15,160 --> 00:03:16,680
Noi, I'm sorry.

16
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:19,400
Hey, what's with all these clothes?

17
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:20,400
Where are you going?

18
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:23,680
If the farm owner is a convicted murderer,

19
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,160
I can't stay here anymore.

20
00:03:25,240 --> 00:03:26,600
He's not just cruel.

21
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:28,640
He's like a madman, a lunatic.

22
00:03:28,720 --> 00:03:30,880
What if one day he acts up

23
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,560
and starts shooting people
like in the news?

24
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:33,840
We're all gonna die.

25
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:35,840
Don't overthink it.

26
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:38,840
Well, this is his family home.

27
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:42,280
He probably just wants to come home.

28
00:03:43,600 --> 00:03:47,080
So that thug is Mr. Yai? Are you sure?

29
00:03:49,880 --> 00:03:52,360
His hair is long and unkempt,

30
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,480
so I didn't notice.

31
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:57,120
But then I saw his face clearly.

32
00:03:57,640 --> 00:03:59,320
He's Yai, no doubt about it.

33
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:02,560
I never thought he'd dare to come back.

34
00:04:02,640 --> 00:04:05,440
If he shows up in court
and says he's still alive,

35
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,440
everything here will be a mess.

36
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,440
He chose to come back now.

37
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:17,720
That means he must have been planning it.

38
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:21,200
I wonder who helped him

39
00:04:21,800 --> 00:04:23,920
get such solid evidence.

40
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,840
MENTAL HEALTH PLAN ASSESSMENT FORM

41
00:04:28,640 --> 00:04:30,280
The police investigation results say that

42
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,640
Pha died in an accident.

43
00:04:33,760 --> 00:04:35,640
This guy had it rough, didn't he?

44
00:04:36,320 --> 00:04:38,680
He was a terrible guy and clumsy too.

45
00:04:39,200 --> 00:04:41,440
I wonder how he could have
gotten himself hit by a car.

46
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:50,360
Your wound's no longer inflamed.

47
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:53,320
You should hurry
and find a place to stay for a while.

48
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,760
Let's make sure Yai doesn't come back.

49
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:57,320
Then we'll talk.

50
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:09,400
When you fully become
the owner of the farm,

51
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,320
don't forget your ex-lover here, alright?

52
00:05:13,880 --> 00:05:15,520
Just hurry up and go.

53
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:18,360
The money is stashed near
the water tank at the back of the farm.

54
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:23,840
Don't forget to walk around the hill,
or someone might see you.

55
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:29,200
Hey.

56
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:32,120
I'm about to get money from my ex-lover.

57
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:35,320
Let's go celebrate.

58
00:05:35,400 --> 00:05:37,320
Hey, get imported booze.

59
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:40,680
Just smelling it
makes me feel like I'm in heaven.

60
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,520
You're the one who killed him?

61
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:11,800
Why?

62
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:18,440
He… He was secretly obsessed with me.

63
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:21,080
He drugged me

64
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,680
and forced himself on me
since the time I lived at the old house.

65
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,720
When he found out
that I married Mr. Paisal,

66
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:32,560
he followed me here
and used the video he had taken

67
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:34,720
to try to blackmail me.

68
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:39,960
He backed me into a corner
until I had no other choice…

69
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:46,640
It's in the past now.

70
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,240
From now on,

71
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,080
I won't let anyone hurt you again.

72
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,160
But now,

73
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,960
the one who will destroy our happiness

74
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:02,480
is Yai.

75
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:04,840
He's back.

76
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:08,480
And the request you submitted
to have him declared missing

77
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:10,160
will be null and void.

78
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:12,360
So what will you do?

79
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,000
He's clearly a criminal.

80
00:07:18,960 --> 00:07:22,360
I'll investigate and find evidence
of the crimes he has committed,

81
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,160
so we can put him in jail.

82
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:26,440
That's going to take too long.

83
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,800
I have a better way.

84
00:07:34,880 --> 00:07:36,560
I probably can't go tonight.

85
00:07:36,640 --> 00:07:38,200
I have to stay and help Madam.

86
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,120
But I'll be there tomorrow morning.

87
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,920
Please take care of Mom for me, Jin.

88
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,040
Thank you so much.

89
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:53,960
Hey, Pin.

90
00:07:54,480 --> 00:07:56,120
Did she win the lottery or something?

91
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:59,200
Look. She ordered a whole feast.

92
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:05,960
How is it?

93
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,360
Is everything ready?

94
00:08:09,880 --> 00:08:12,400
Are you expecting guests, Madam?

95
00:08:14,080 --> 00:08:15,360
Is this really a good idea?

96
00:08:15,440 --> 00:08:17,880
Mr. Yai is still upstairs. I'm afraid…

97
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:21,240
Who else would be a special guest

98
00:08:21,320 --> 00:08:23,280
besides Mr. Yai,

99
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,680
the only heir to Paisal Farm?

100
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:29,360
- Noi.
- Yes?

101
00:08:29,440 --> 00:08:31,480
Go get Mr. Yai.

102
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:34,280
Tell him I'm inviting him to dinner.

103
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,720
Are your ears ringing?

104
00:08:43,240 --> 00:08:45,480
Pin, I'm scared.

105
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:48,160
What if he gets upset and cuts me?

106
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,960
Don't be silly, Noi.

107
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:51,880
Mr. Yai wouldn't do that.

108
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,760
I'll go myself, then.

109
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:59,200
Oh, I'm so, so hungry.

110
00:08:59,800 --> 00:09:03,200
The smell of food
floated all the way upstairs.

111
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:08,120
Whoa. Wow, wow.

112
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:11,800
You're going all out, aren't you, Auntie?

113
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:18,200
Wow, so lavish and impressive. Whoo!

114
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:22,440
I thought it would be
a simple, chill family dinner,

115
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,600
so I'm only wearing my comfy pajamas.

116
00:09:24,680 --> 00:09:26,200
It's okay,

117
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,200
just dress how you like.

118
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:31,400
And this outfit
looks good in a different way.

119
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:41,400
Don't stare too long, girls. I'm shy.

120
00:10:04,400 --> 00:10:05,400
Uh…

121
00:10:06,520 --> 00:10:08,440
- I must apologize to you.
- Hey!

122
00:10:10,680 --> 00:10:11,560
Don't do that.

123
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:12,920
No, don't bow to me like that.

124
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:15,080
That makes me feel old.

125
00:10:15,160 --> 00:10:17,440
Come on, we're grown men.

126
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:20,920
A little clash now and then
is no big deal.

127
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,400
That's good to hear.

128
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:42,200
Let's drink to our friendship, Mr. Yai.

129
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:45,640
Let's celebrate being together again.

130
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:48,040
Pin.

131
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:50,200
Come drink together. Sit down.

132
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:53,800
Uh… I don't drink alcohol.

133
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:56,000
Ugh, I forgot you're a nun.

134
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,840
Then just drink water. Here.

135
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:02,280
Pin's duty is to take care of things,

136
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:03,760
to serve us.

137
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,800
She's serving me, isn't she?

138
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:09,200
Come. Here. Sit.

139
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:14,400
Raise your glasses!

140
00:11:16,160 --> 00:11:18,120
To a happy family!

141
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:33,000
What kind of drink is this? It's terrible.

142
00:11:33,080 --> 00:11:34,240
Huh?

143
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,720
This is sour and bitter
at the same time. Ew…

144
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,120
It's no match for 28% liquor.

145
00:11:41,560 --> 00:11:43,560
That's a French wine.
It costs 10,000 per bottle.

146
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:46,560
Have you been living underground?

147
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:49,080
- Teera.
- Whoa. Oh, my.

148
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:51,120
10,000 baht per bottle?

149
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:59,600
Maybe one day I'll brew
some good old white spirit for you.

150
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:00,840
You'll love it.

151
00:12:00,920 --> 00:12:02,320
It's okay, really.

152
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,000
I don't think it's to my taste.

153
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:06,440
But I ordered this meal
from a luxury hotel.

154
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:08,920
Everything is guaranteed to be delicious.

155
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:11,360
Sit down and let's eat together, okay?

156
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:14,760
Come. Sit down.

157
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:25,840
Uncle Win, are you sure
Mr. Yai is really Mr. Paisal's son?

158
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:28,560
From the look of him,
he's more likely here to rob the farm

159
00:12:28,640 --> 00:12:30,160
than to save it.

160
00:12:31,880 --> 00:12:32,760
What's Mr. Yai like?

161
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:36,160
He isn't a drunk nor is he crazy.

162
00:12:36,240 --> 00:12:38,400
His mood swings up and down

163
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,080
like a rollercoaster.

164
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:41,880
I can't explain it.

165
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,120
What do you think, Piak?

166
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,800
If you ask me,

167
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:47,040
I think he's high on weed.

168
00:12:47,120 --> 00:12:48,400
The man is a total stoner.

169
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:50,640
Then what Madam said
about him fleeing the farm

170
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:52,680
because he killed someone
is true, right, Dad?

171
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,040
You're stunned?

172
00:12:58,120 --> 00:13:00,440
If you know something juicy, just tell us.

173
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:02,120
- Yeah.
- We're listening.

174
00:13:10,280 --> 00:13:12,120
If I haven't seen it with my own eyes,

175
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,880
I won't speak of it or even believe it.

176
00:13:16,200 --> 00:13:18,880
Oh? Wait, Uncle. Let's talk more.

177
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:20,440
What?

178
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:21,800
Ugh.

179
00:13:21,880 --> 00:13:25,040
Oh, what if Mr. Yai really is a fugitive?

180
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,720
Won't the farm be ruined even more?

181
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:29,240
Ah! Just the thought of it
stresses me out.

182
00:13:29,320 --> 00:13:30,720
Dear, I'm scared.

183
00:14:03,840 --> 00:14:06,040
Oh? Dig in, Auntie.

184
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:10,600
I'm already happy to see you enjoying it.

185
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,920
Ever since you disappeared,

186
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:17,480
we've been looking everywhere for you.

187
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:21,200
Why didn't you contact me?

188
00:14:22,880 --> 00:14:25,120
I fled and hid near the border.

189
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:27,640
Oh.

190
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:28,760
That sounds terrible.

191
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:31,400
And who have you been with?

192
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:33,120
How did you survive…

193
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:39,240
How did you manage
to stay safe until today?

194
00:14:44,040 --> 00:14:46,360
I tried many ways to earn money, Auntie.

195
00:14:47,240 --> 00:14:48,840
But the one I remember best

196
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:52,200
was cooking and supplying black dogs

197
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:56,000
to restaurants near the border.

198
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,200
How did you do that?

199
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:02,840
The owner would bring us black dogs.

200
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:05,160
Black dogs pay very well, you know.

201
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:09,280
People say they have nourishing qualities.

202
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,800
I've heard something along those lines.

203
00:15:15,560 --> 00:15:17,880
But slaughtering them was fun.

204
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,600
I would stuff them into sacks

205
00:15:23,680 --> 00:15:26,400
and submerge them until they vomited

206
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,520
and pooped.

207
00:15:30,760 --> 00:15:31,840
Oh.

208
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:36,040
Sorry… Defecated all the waste.

209
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,040
After that,

210
00:15:40,120 --> 00:15:42,320
I'd pull them from the water,

211
00:15:42,400 --> 00:15:44,680
clean them,

212
00:15:45,520 --> 00:15:48,240
and boil them in large tin cans.

213
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:52,360
After plucking their fur off,

214
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:55,200
I'd place them on a chopping block,

215
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:56,920
flip them over,

216
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,120
sever their necks,

217
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:02,320
and slice them straight down to the tail.

218
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:08,440
Their innards must be cooked
in boiling water,

219
00:16:08,520 --> 00:16:10,040
or they'll stink.

220
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,440
Care to try some, Auntie?

221
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:15,080
I guarantee you,
the first taste will capture you,

222
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,960
but the rest won't stick in your throat.

223
00:16:17,040 --> 00:16:18,880
The taste is unique every time

224
00:16:18,960 --> 00:16:21,360
because the recipe is random, Auntie.

225
00:16:32,160 --> 00:16:35,040
And another great dish, Manager,

226
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:38,000
is minced dog with basil.

227
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:39,920
I'd cut their tongues

228
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:43,440
and ears and mince them together

229
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,560
so that it'd be nice and crispy. Here.

230
00:16:48,520 --> 00:16:51,240
This squid with basil
doesn't even come close.

231
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:52,440
It's child's play.

232
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:54,800
Try it. Here.

233
00:16:56,480 --> 00:16:57,520
Taste it.

234
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,000
Please excuse me.

235
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:12,599
Ugh.

236
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:15,160
Why are you sitting there tearing up?

237
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:19,319
I can't believe

238
00:17:19,839 --> 00:17:21,599
you've turned into someone like this.

239
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:25,440
I've done worse, Pinanong.

240
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:27,280
Do you want to hear more?

241
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:33,240
I've sliced snakes open
to extract their gall.

242
00:17:34,080 --> 00:17:35,880
It was absolutely amazing.

243
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,840
They were struggling, and I…

244
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:40,800
Pin, where are you going?
I haven't finished telling you.

245
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:46,000
Mr. Yai?

246
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,520
Yai's disgusting.

247
00:18:05,720 --> 00:18:08,120
He's been mean like this
since he was a boy.

248
00:18:08,200 --> 00:18:11,320
But now, he's far worse.

249
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:15,000
He must have picked up those habits
during his time with thieves.

250
00:18:15,720 --> 00:18:18,120
Then he could attack us at any time.

251
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:21,960
And I think giving him a false sense
of security before eliminating him

252
00:18:22,040 --> 00:18:23,360
would take too long.

253
00:18:23,960 --> 00:18:26,240
Madam! Madam!

254
00:18:26,320 --> 00:18:28,680
Madam! Madam!

255
00:18:28,760 --> 00:18:30,440
Mr. Yai! Mr. Yai…

256
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:31,880
What are you trying to say?

257
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:34,360
Uh… It's…

258
00:18:34,440 --> 00:18:36,280
Uh… Ugh.

259
00:18:36,360 --> 00:18:38,400
Mr. Yai, what's wrong?

260
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:42,040
You… You poisoned me.

261
00:18:44,560 --> 00:18:47,400
Mr. Yai, stop being childish
and joking around.

262
00:18:47,480 --> 00:18:48,320
Enough.

263
00:18:50,720 --> 00:18:52,480
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

264
00:18:53,720 --> 00:18:54,560
Mr. Yai.

265
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:57,240
What's happening?

266
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:00,040
I don't know what's wrong with him.

267
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:01,560
Please call an ambulance.

268
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,640
You… You…

269
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:06,880
You poisoned me…

270
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,080
- You… Teera.
- Mr. Yai.

271
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:10,920
You poisoned me!

272
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,440
- Ah!
- No. Stop!

273
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:13,960
- Mr. Yai!
- Mr. Yai!

274
00:19:14,040 --> 00:19:14,880
- Help!
- Let go of him.

275
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:15,840
Help me.

276
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:16,880
- Mr. Yai, let go!
- Help,

277
00:19:16,960 --> 00:19:18,400
- Krongsuk.
- I…

278
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:21,400
- Mr. Yai!
- I won't die alone.

279
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:25,160
- Let go of him!
- You need to take care of yourself first.

280
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,200
Please let go.

281
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:27,440
Let go of him.

282
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,520
- Hey.
- Whoa, Mr. Yai.

283
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,440
Mr. Yai.

284
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:35,240
- Noi, call an ambulance. Hurry.
- Yes?

285
00:19:35,320 --> 00:19:37,080
- Ambulance…
- Mr. Yai.

286
00:19:37,160 --> 00:19:38,280
What's the number, Pin?

287
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:39,800
It's 1669.

288
00:19:39,880 --> 00:19:41,560
- One-Six-Six-Six…
- One-Six-Six-Nine.

289
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:43,040
- Six-Six-Nine?
- One-Six-Six-Nine.

290
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,480
No need!

291
00:19:59,640 --> 00:20:01,120
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

292
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:02,800
Mr. Yai.

293
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:05,000
He's unconscious.

294
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:06,840
Should we take him to a doctor?

295
00:20:08,080 --> 00:20:10,200
It's probably food poisoning.

296
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:13,360
Maybe he's never eaten
anything good in his life.

297
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:16,200
You stay here. I'll go get the medicine.

298
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,720
But he could die.

299
00:20:22,200 --> 00:20:25,280
I'm sorry, but he…

300
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:33,960
Mr. Yai.

301
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,120
Hey.

302
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:39,880
So it was your doing?

303
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,320
It wasn't me.

304
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:43,400
You said you'd get him
to let his guard down first.

305
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:49,800
It's probably not his destiny
to own Paisal Farm.

306
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,000
What's that?

307
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:02,280
A magic medicine

308
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:05,520
to free Yai from his suffering.

309
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:09,880
Mr. Yai.

310
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:11,840
Mr. Yai.

311
00:21:12,800 --> 00:21:13,800
Mr. Yai.

312
00:21:17,120 --> 00:21:18,440
I can't wait anymore.

313
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,680
Pin!

314
00:21:35,760 --> 00:21:37,800
I told you to stay put.

315
00:21:37,880 --> 00:21:39,840
Didn't you understand what I said?

316
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:41,880
I'll take Mr. Yai to the doctor.

317
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:43,560
He's still unconscious.

318
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:45,120
Then,

319
00:21:45,200 --> 00:21:47,880
let Mr. Yai take this medicine first.

320
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,480
What is it?

321
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:54,160
Even if I told you the name,
you wouldn't know it.

322
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,240
He must have been allergic
to something in the food.

323
00:21:56,320 --> 00:21:58,920
This medicine can help with allergies.

324
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,760
Teera.

325
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,440
Mr. Yai.

326
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:43,160
Huh?

327
00:22:43,680 --> 00:22:44,760
Mr. Yai.

328
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:46,600
Mr. Yai.

329
00:22:50,560 --> 00:22:51,840
Why is this happening?

330
00:22:51,920 --> 00:22:53,240
We should take him to a doctor.

331
00:22:54,760 --> 00:22:56,760
Pin, move aside.

332
00:22:56,840 --> 00:22:58,960
Teera, check on him.

333
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:04,480
Mr. Yai.

334
00:23:04,560 --> 00:23:05,760
Mr. Yai.

335
00:23:06,280 --> 00:23:07,120
Mr. Yai.

336
00:23:08,120 --> 00:23:09,120
Mr. Yai.

337
00:23:10,560 --> 00:23:13,400
Mr. Yai. Mr. Yai.

338
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,360
Mr. Yai?

339
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:28,320
Ugh…

340
00:23:29,080 --> 00:23:30,400
I'm sorry, Manager.

341
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:31,840
I felt so nauseous.

342
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:35,240
I should have seen it coming
the moment you ran off and threw up.

343
00:23:38,760 --> 00:23:39,840
Mr. Yai.

344
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:42,160
Are you sure you're okay?

345
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,480
I was so worried about you.

346
00:23:44,480 --> 00:23:46,000
Of course, I'm not.

347
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:49,040
Here. I can barely keep it in.
You see? Oh, my.

348
00:23:52,720 --> 00:23:54,160
It's not good to eat food from outside.

349
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:56,320
Not that delicious,
but clearly a biohazard. Pin.

350
00:23:57,320 --> 00:24:00,000
From now, you have to cook
every meal for me.

351
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:03,160
My poopy's here.

352
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,520
Give me a moment.

353
00:24:43,200 --> 00:24:44,160
Mr. Paisal?

354
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:48,400
Paisal Farm will only belong to my son!

355
00:24:48,480 --> 00:24:49,720
Remember that!

356
00:24:52,080 --> 00:24:53,360
Let go of me.

357
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,480
Let go.

358
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:56,640
Let go of me! Let go!

359
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:14,360
What do you want
this early in the morning?

360
00:25:14,440 --> 00:25:16,240
It's something important.

361
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:18,720
Yai's dead?

362
00:25:19,360 --> 00:25:20,760
Uh, no, Madam.

363
00:25:20,840 --> 00:25:22,160
He's still asleep.

364
00:25:23,720 --> 00:25:25,000
Then what is it?

365
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:27,920
Well…

366
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,960
I'd like to request
an advance on my salary

367
00:25:31,040 --> 00:25:33,080
to cover my mom's heart surgery.

368
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:34,960
- How much?
- 300,000 baht.

369
00:25:35,560 --> 00:25:36,800
300,000?!

370
00:25:38,120 --> 00:25:40,280
What kind of surgery costs 300,000?

371
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,720
Here are the details
from the hospital, Madam.

372
00:25:49,280 --> 00:25:50,520
I won't understand this,

373
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:51,800
and I don't have that money.

374
00:25:52,400 --> 00:25:54,920
Hey, do you know how much I have to cover

375
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,240
for the farm's expenses?

376
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:57,640
Let alone my other expenses.

377
00:25:57,720 --> 00:25:58,560
I don't have that.

378
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,360
- But… Madam…
- Oh.

379
00:26:01,440 --> 00:26:03,600
There's someone you can ask.

380
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:04,880
It's Mr. Yai.

381
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:07,240
He went around claiming
ownership of Paisal Farm.

382
00:26:07,320 --> 00:26:10,080
So, go ask him. Go.

383
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,000
Madam.

384
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:17,880
We don't have any cash right now.

385
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:20,880
I'd like to ask if I could pay
in monthly installments.

386
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:23,720
We do not have a payment plan policy.

387
00:27:23,800 --> 00:27:25,960
- Well…
- Could you please help me?

388
00:27:26,040 --> 00:27:27,640
Keep my ID as a guarantee.

389
00:27:27,720 --> 00:27:29,680
I promise I won't default on my payments.

390
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:31,000
Please.

391
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:34,400
I was just about to tell you
that someone has paid for everything.

392
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:36,000
It was already paid?

393
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,040
Who paid it?

394
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:41,240
The payment
was received via mobile banking.

395
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:42,480
The patient's name was provided,

396
00:27:42,560 --> 00:27:45,000
but the name of the person
making the transfer was not.

397
00:27:45,080 --> 00:27:46,600
Here's the receipt.

398
00:27:48,120 --> 00:27:49,240
Here.

399
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:50,400
Thank you.

400
00:28:02,520 --> 00:28:03,440
Jin.

401
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:06,480
Did you take care
of my mom's medical bill?

402
00:28:10,120 --> 00:28:11,120
No, I didn't.

403
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:14,320
Where would I find 300,000 baht?

404
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:17,680
Pin.

405
00:28:20,480 --> 00:28:22,960
The surgery costs 300,000?

406
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:27,520
Didn't you tell me
it doesn't cost that much?

407
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:31,360
No, I don't want to be treated.

408
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:34,640
- I'd rather die than have to borrow money!
- Mom.

409
00:28:34,720 --> 00:28:35,880
- No.
- Mom, listen to me.

410
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,800
Madam paid for it.

411
00:28:38,840 --> 00:28:40,280
Madam already paid for it.

412
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:43,000
Here's the receipt.

413
00:28:59,760 --> 00:29:01,080
Oh…

414
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,200
My dear Madam.

415
00:29:05,360 --> 00:29:07,120
You have never abandoned me,

416
00:29:07,640 --> 00:29:10,120
through good times and bad.

417
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:15,040
If Madam's father

418
00:29:15,120 --> 00:29:17,400
hadn't brought me home that day,

419
00:29:19,560 --> 00:29:21,560
provided me food and water,

420
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,640
and sheltered me,

421
00:29:25,840 --> 00:29:29,200
I would have died beside the trash pile.

422
00:29:30,440 --> 00:29:31,640
Mom.

423
00:29:32,280 --> 00:29:35,360
You said you wouldn't
talk about it anymore.

424
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:41,240
Pin, I want you to remember

425
00:29:42,080 --> 00:29:44,160
that our lives, yours and mine,

426
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:46,600
have survived to this day

427
00:29:48,040 --> 00:29:50,680
because of Madam's family, okay?

428
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:55,720
You must repay their kindness.

429
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,320
Even if it costs us our lives,

430
00:29:59,240 --> 00:30:01,040
we must give it to her.

431
00:30:02,560 --> 00:30:03,920
Do you understand?

432
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:09,800
Yes.

433
00:30:16,480 --> 00:30:20,440
Are you sure it was Madam Frugal's money?

434
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:24,000
I asked her to borrow money.

435
00:30:24,080 --> 00:30:26,280
No one else knows about it except for Noi.

436
00:30:26,360 --> 00:30:28,240
And we can count Noi out.

437
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:31,720
That leaves Madam
as the only one capable of paying it.

438
00:30:33,320 --> 00:30:35,680
So why aren't you letting Aunt Un
return to the farm

439
00:30:35,760 --> 00:30:37,880
so you can find out who it really was?

440
00:30:37,960 --> 00:30:40,160
There's trouble at the farm now.

441
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:43,680
Mr. Yai, Mr. Paisal's son, came back.

442
00:30:44,960 --> 00:30:45,960
The one

443
00:30:46,720 --> 00:30:48,960
who killed a worker?

444
00:30:49,040 --> 00:30:50,000
Jin.

445
00:31:42,360 --> 00:31:44,600
Pha. Pha.

446
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:45,800
Pha.

447
00:31:50,880 --> 00:31:51,760
You…

448
00:31:52,560 --> 00:31:54,040
You killed a man.

449
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:55,600
I didn't do it.

450
00:31:58,400 --> 00:31:59,600
Run away.

451
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:01,600
And don't ever come back.

452
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,480
And I won't tell anyone

453
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:06,960
that you're a murderer.

454
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:09,000
You murderer.

455
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:11,080
You murderer. You murderer.

456
00:32:23,040 --> 00:32:25,280
Hey, who are you?

457
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:34,880
Who the hell are you?

458
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:36,320
What are you doing in here?

459
00:32:38,080 --> 00:32:39,200
A worker, huh?

460
00:32:39,280 --> 00:32:41,320
The barn door isn't working well.
Just fix it.

461
00:32:44,160 --> 00:32:45,920
Paisal Farm isn't a place to go
for an afternoon stroll.

462
00:32:46,880 --> 00:32:49,720
Well, I like breaking the rules.

463
00:33:07,080 --> 00:33:08,040
Come here!

464
00:33:43,040 --> 00:33:45,480
Hey! Ah… Jom, wait!

465
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:47,480
Wait, Jom. Wait, wait.

466
00:33:48,080 --> 00:33:51,040
- Stop.
- Let go of me, Piak. He's trespassing!

467
00:33:51,560 --> 00:33:52,640
Ugh.

468
00:34:00,520 --> 00:34:02,480
Hey, stop it, Jom! Wait!

469
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:04,280
Wait, wait.

470
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,160
Piak.

471
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:08,719
Jom.

472
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:12,159
Stop it right now.

473
00:34:12,239 --> 00:34:14,280
Dad. Bring others to subdue him.

474
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:15,400
He's stealing from us.

475
00:34:28,080 --> 00:34:30,040
Apologize to Mr. Yai right now.

476
00:34:40,880 --> 00:34:42,199
I'm sorry.

477
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:44,960
Are your hands only good for fighting?

478
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,719
Bow to him respectfully.

479
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:49,960
Hey.

480
00:34:51,560 --> 00:34:52,920
Just broke a little sweat.

481
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,639
It's nothing, Uncle.

482
00:34:54,719 --> 00:34:57,400
I've done much more
than this with my crew.

483
00:35:02,560 --> 00:35:04,360
No hard feelings, alright?

484
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:08,080
But your son's quite skilled.

485
00:35:10,080 --> 00:35:11,560
This guy's a hothead,

486
00:35:12,320 --> 00:35:14,200
always resorting to violence.

487
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:20,520
You're Jom, right?

488
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:24,040
I heard Uncle Win had one son.

489
00:35:26,560 --> 00:35:28,080
I separated from his mother.

490
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:30,720
When she died,
I took him in to live with me.

491
00:35:31,760 --> 00:35:33,640
But you had already run away back then.

492
00:35:35,640 --> 00:35:38,280
And my name's Waan. I'm a life coach.

493
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:41,440
I specialize in coaching
my husband, actually.

494
00:35:41,520 --> 00:35:43,600
Ooh, sorry, sorry.

495
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:46,040
Uh… I'm Piak.

496
00:35:46,120 --> 00:35:47,960
Uncle Win took me in to work here.

497
00:35:56,840 --> 00:35:59,440
It seems you have a problem
with my outfit.

498
00:35:59,960 --> 00:36:01,640
It's my style.

499
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:05,040
I haven't washed these jeans
for almost a year.

500
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:07,280
Take them off,
and they would stand on their own.

501
00:36:12,000 --> 00:36:13,720
You've changed a lot, Mr. Yai.

502
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:18,240
Why?

503
00:36:18,760 --> 00:36:22,640
It doesn't suit
the only heir to Paisal Farm, right?

504
00:36:35,640 --> 00:36:36,480
Hey!

505
00:36:37,520 --> 00:36:38,400
Hey!

506
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:40,840
Hey!

507
00:36:45,480 --> 00:36:46,600
Hey, go with them!

508
00:36:46,680 --> 00:36:48,000
- But I'll get hurt.
- You two!

509
00:36:48,080 --> 00:36:49,480
- Yeah, just go!
- Alright.

510
00:36:52,440 --> 00:36:54,560
Hey! What are you doing here?!

511
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:05,920
Whoa, no! Mr. Yai, don't shoot!

512
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:06,840
Don't shoot.

513
00:37:07,520 --> 00:37:09,200
Madam hired these two to work here.

514
00:37:09,920 --> 00:37:12,000
Last time, it was a misunderstanding.

515
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:15,600
The existing workers
haven't even been paid.

516
00:37:15,680 --> 00:37:17,320
How was she able to hire new ones?

517
00:37:26,400 --> 00:37:28,160
Well, well. It's okay.

518
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:31,840
The more there are,
the louder the clinking of glasses.

519
00:37:31,920 --> 00:37:33,400
It would sound great!

520
00:37:34,760 --> 00:37:36,320
As for the outstanding salary,

521
00:37:36,400 --> 00:37:37,960
I'll arrange it for you all.

522
00:37:38,040 --> 00:37:40,640
That's who I am, bold and dependable.

523
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:43,600
I'm able to mingle with every faction,
and I love all of you.

524
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:53,320
This morning,

525
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:56,480
you just asked me to transfer 300,000 baht
for Pinanong's mom's medical bill.

526
00:37:57,000 --> 00:37:59,160
Now you're asking for another 500,000?

527
00:38:00,720 --> 00:38:02,480
<i>The money from this morning was from Tong.</i>

528
00:38:02,560 --> 00:38:04,160
<i>I didn't spend a single baht.</i>

529
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:07,000
<i>Your money is like mine.</i>

530
00:38:07,080 --> 00:38:08,800
<i>You can't just squander it.</i>

531
00:38:12,080 --> 00:38:13,840
Don't you want me to inherit the farm?

532
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:17,400
Strategic warfare is the only way.

533
00:38:17,480 --> 00:38:19,640
Win the war
by first winning over the enemy.

534
00:38:21,120 --> 00:38:23,800
And you said you're going to file
a petition to have the court

535
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,920
revoke the order declaring you missing.

536
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,880
When are you going to go see my professor?

537
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:33,960
Uh… Yai? Hold on.

538
00:38:35,920 --> 00:38:37,440
What a scumbag friend.

539
00:38:41,000 --> 00:38:43,080
- Babe…
- What the hell are they doing?

540
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:44,840
Do they have no shame at all?

541
00:38:58,280 --> 00:38:59,640
Open the door.

542
00:39:07,120 --> 00:39:08,160
Ma'am.

543
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,440
You can have fun however you want,

544
00:39:10,520 --> 00:39:12,200
but be considerate of the next room.

545
00:39:12,720 --> 00:39:14,680
This is a hotel, not a bar.

546
00:39:15,600 --> 00:39:17,160
I can report you to the police.

547
00:39:17,960 --> 00:39:18,920
What?

548
00:39:19,440 --> 00:39:22,600
You're jealous
that we're having a good time?

549
00:39:26,080 --> 00:39:28,200
You're sad and alone, huh?

550
00:39:30,680 --> 00:39:32,680
Wanna join the fun? Come on.

551
00:39:33,480 --> 00:39:34,800
- Are you ready?
- Hm?

552
00:39:35,320 --> 00:39:37,240
I'm ready for you to say "action".

553
00:39:38,680 --> 00:39:39,880
Who's this pointy-faced guy?

554
00:39:40,840 --> 00:39:42,200
Don't bother with him.

555
00:39:42,280 --> 00:39:44,000
Just a party pooper.

556
00:39:45,040 --> 00:39:46,840
Who? Who's the party pooper?

557
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:48,120
Huh? Who did that?

558
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:53,240
Ugh!

559
00:39:53,320 --> 00:39:54,760
Just don't be loud!

560
00:40:01,480 --> 00:40:04,480
Does Yai have that much money
to pay all their salaries?

561
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:07,080
He must have stolen it.

562
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:09,360
Maybe he's even using
our farm to launder it.

563
00:40:10,680 --> 00:40:13,120
Fine. Let him pay.

564
00:40:13,200 --> 00:40:15,880
He's all talk, apparently.

565
00:40:18,680 --> 00:40:20,680
And what are you going to do with him?

566
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,480
Mr. Na's about to come back.

567
00:40:23,600 --> 00:40:25,480
I already texted him,

568
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:27,720
telling him to stay
and travel for a few weeks

569
00:40:27,800 --> 00:40:29,560
because the farm is being renovated.

570
00:40:30,080 --> 00:40:31,880
But he hasn't responded yet.

571
00:40:35,680 --> 00:40:37,000
That's not Na.

572
00:40:37,920 --> 00:40:39,320
But it's Nee.

573
00:40:41,240 --> 00:40:42,680
What's going on this time?

574
00:40:47,800 --> 00:40:49,760
<i>Babe…</i>

575
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:56,080
TATSANEE

576
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:57,840
<i>Auntie,</i>

577
00:40:57,920 --> 00:41:01,080
<i>why aren't you transferring money to Pon?</i>

578
00:41:01,160 --> 00:41:04,320
<i>He's threatened</i>
<i>to post the clip to porn sites!</i>

579
00:41:08,720 --> 00:41:09,760
Again?

580
00:41:50,360 --> 00:41:51,320
Huh?

581
00:41:52,080 --> 00:41:54,320
Auntie hasn't transferred
the money to you yet?

582
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:57,000
It's okay.

583
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:59,720
It's okay if she refuses to transfer.

584
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:01,520
Wait for me there, babe.

585
00:42:01,600 --> 00:42:03,680
I'll bring the money to you myself.

586
00:42:15,680 --> 00:42:17,240
Hey, you.

587
00:42:22,680 --> 00:42:23,960
Yeah, you.

588
00:42:25,920 --> 00:42:26,880
You're talking to me, ma'am?

589
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:29,560
I'll slap you.

590
00:42:29,640 --> 00:42:30,960
Don't call me ma'am.

591
00:42:31,040 --> 00:42:33,240
Call me Ms. Tatsanee.

592
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:35,400
Come here.

593
00:42:40,800 --> 00:42:42,600
Is anyone home?

594
00:42:45,720 --> 00:42:46,880
Only Noi.

595
00:42:53,640 --> 00:42:55,200
Follow me.

596
00:43:05,480 --> 00:43:06,320
Oh?

597
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:07,840
Hurry up.

598
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:08,920
Once the job's done,

599
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:11,800
I'll give you another 500 as compensation.

600
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:54,880
Hey. Put these in my car.

601
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:56,160
Be careful not to break them.

602
00:44:03,320 --> 00:44:04,600
‪Idiot! You idiot!

603
00:44:05,600 --> 00:44:07,160
You idiot…

604
00:44:11,960 --> 00:44:13,600
My French perfume,

605
00:44:13,680 --> 00:44:16,960
my gold and sea pearls serum,
they're all ruined.

606
00:44:18,440 --> 00:44:19,360
You idiot.

607
00:44:19,440 --> 00:44:20,880
You idiot.

608
00:44:20,960 --> 00:44:21,880
You hillbilly.

609
00:44:21,960 --> 00:44:24,800
Don't you know
I need these for my live selling?

610
00:44:24,880 --> 00:44:27,800
They cost so much money.

611
00:44:28,320 --> 00:44:30,120
I've never even used a single bottle.

612
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:31,680
Oh, calm down, ma'am.

613
00:44:31,760 --> 00:44:33,680
I'll buy them all back for you later.

614
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:37,160
Someone like you?

615
00:44:39,200 --> 00:44:40,960
Buying all of them back for me?

616
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:50,280
What's this thing?

617
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:58,160
Oh! A whitening deodorant roll-on
that eliminates armpit odor.

618
00:44:58,240 --> 00:44:59,120
Come on, ma'am.

619
00:44:59,200 --> 00:45:02,400
I'll just by you two alum crystals
for you to dip in water.

620
00:45:02,480 --> 00:45:05,640
Then you can smoothen the sharp edges
with your foot

621
00:45:05,720 --> 00:45:07,320
then apply it on your armpit.

622
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:09,360
I guarantee you the results
are just as good.

623
00:45:09,440 --> 00:45:13,720
Your armpit hair will be soft and silky.

624
00:45:15,000 --> 00:45:16,440
You filthy bastard!

625
00:45:17,320 --> 00:45:18,520
Rub the alum with your foot?

626
00:45:18,600 --> 00:45:20,200
Just use it on your face!

627
00:45:21,920 --> 00:45:22,880
You'll see.

628
00:45:23,600 --> 00:45:25,680
I'll tell Auntie to fire you!

629
00:45:43,200 --> 00:45:45,280
Thieves only have one rule.

630
00:45:45,360 --> 00:45:46,160
Be the first one to kill.

631
00:45:46,240 --> 00:45:47,840
If you dare to swing
that axe at me, just do it.

632
00:45:47,920 --> 00:45:50,520
It's my love and my memory.

633
00:45:50,600 --> 00:45:52,600
<i>Do what I taught you to do,</i>

634
00:45:52,680 --> 00:45:55,520
<i>and you'll get everything</i>
<i>that belonged to that old man Paisal.</i>

635
00:45:57,240 --> 00:45:59,280
- It's not beating fast.
- Listen carefully.

636
00:45:59,360 --> 00:46:00,400
Ugh.

637
00:46:00,480 --> 00:46:03,680
And why don't you use Pin
to tempt Yai instead of me?

638
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:06,840
It's obvious that she's leading Yai on.

639
00:46:46,960 --> 00:46:49,160
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
